  <main id="ds-main">
    <header class="ds-intro" id="overview">
      <p class="ds-kicker">Intent-driven · UI concept</p>
      <h1>New-Map Authoring</h1>
      <p>
        Today the studio runs <strong>structure → meaning</strong>: it parses a map's XML, then
        <em>derives</em> what each region means. New-map authoring runs the other way —
        <strong>meaning → structure</strong>. The author states intent (identity, teams, spawns, build
        space, wools) and the system <em>generates</em> the region / filter / apply-rule graph that
        serializes to PGM-loadable XML. This page lays out every step of that experience and the panels
        it uses, with canvases drawn from the <em>real</em> region geometry of <code>thunder</code> — a
        four-team 90°-rotational map — so a blank copy (<code>thunder_blank</code>) could, in theory, be
        authored end-to-end to a valid export. It reuses the existing design system; the only new
        primitive is the clean <code>flow-steps</code> sub-step bar.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- ════════════════════════ FLOW OVERVIEW ════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="ds-section" id="flow">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="ds-kicker">The flow</p>
          <h2>Six phases, one gate — define each thing once</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Dead-simple and guided: identity and world come first, each step shapes one slice of intent,
           and a playability gate closes the loop before export.</p>
      </div>

      <article class="ds-example">
        <div class="ds-example-label">Authoring pipeline — world seeds it, traversability gates it</div>
        <div class="ds-panel-frame">
          <div class="workspace-scroll">
            <section class="panel-section">
              <div class="section-header section-header--ruled">
                <h2 class="section-title">Phases</h2>
                <span class="badge badge--dim">thunder_blank</span>
              </div>
              <div class="section-body">
                <div class="step-row">
                  <span class="step-dot step-dot--done"></span>
                  <span class="step-label">0 · Map Info</span>
                  <span class="step-detail">The basics the generator needs — map name and authors. Version, mode, objective auto-derived.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="step-row">
                  <span class="step-dot step-dot--done"></span>
                  <span class="step-label">1 · World</span>
                  <span class="step-detail">Detect the terrain — neutral island shapes + symmetry. Seeds team count and spawn positions.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="step-row">
                  <span class="step-dot"></span>
                  <span class="step-label">2 · Teams</span>
                  <span class="step-detail">Define teams; assign islands (orbit order); place team 0's spawn + protection once — orbit fills the rest.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="step-row">
                  <span class="step-dot"></span>
                  <span class="step-label">3 · Build</span>
                  <span class="step-detail">Set the max build height in a side view; draw the over-void bridges. The terrain is already buildable.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="step-row">
                  <span class="step-dot"></span>
                  <span class="step-label">4 · Wools</span>
                  <span class="step-detail">Colour → spawn → room → monuments, one sub-step at a time; orbit fills the rest; rules auto-wired.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="step-row">
                  <span class="step-dot step-dot--running"></span>
                  <span class="step-label">5 · Review</span>
                  <span class="step-detail">Round-trip · mirror-consistency · buildability · traversability gate — then export the XML.</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="section-footer section-footer--separated">
                <div class="panel-warning">
                  <strong>Build ⇄ Traversability is a loop.</strong> The closing gate is computed over the
                  build / bridge geometry, so <em>build must precede wools</em>. If a spawn can't reach a wool,
                  the gate sends you back to Build to add a bridge — it is not a separate step, it is the
                  condition for export.
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <!-- ════════════════════════ NAVIGATION MODEL ════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="ds-section" id="nav">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="ds-kicker">Navigation</p>
          <h2>The navigation model</h2>
        </div>
        <p>A guided wizard at three levels: jump between phases on the rail, walk the sub-steps with the
           flow bar, advance linearly with Back / Next.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        Authoring is a guided wizard, not a free-form editor. The <strong>activity rail</strong> (left) holds
        the six phases and lets you jump to any unlocked one — completed phases carry a green dot, the current
        one a left bar. Inside a phase, the <strong>flow bar</strong> (a clean step strip in the canvas
        sub-bar) walks the sub-steps — a check marks done, an accent underline marks the current one.
        <strong>Back / Next</strong> advances linearly. No numbered-circle bars: the chrome stays quiet so the
        map stays the focus.
      </p>

      <div class="ds-example-grid">
        <article class="ds-example">
          <div class="ds-example-label">Phases — the activity rail</div>
          <div class="ds-panel-frame" style="display:flex">
            <nav class="activity-rail">
              <div class="activity-logo">
                <div class="activity-logo-box">
                  <span class="activity-logo-pgm">pgm</span>
                  <span class="activity-logo-sub">STUDIO</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <button class="activity-btn" data-status="green" title="Map Info"><i data-lucide="book-open-text"></i></button>
              <button class="activity-btn" data-status="green" title="World"><i data-lucide="settings-2"></i></button>
              <button class="activity-btn" data-status="green" title="Teams"><i data-lucide="users"></i></button>
              <button class="activity-btn active" title="Build"><i data-lucide="pickaxe"></i></button>
              <button class="activity-btn" title="Wools"><i data-lucide="goal"></i></button>
              <button class="activity-btn" title="Review"><i data-lucide="badge-check"></i></button>
            </nav>
            <div class="workspace-scroll" style="flex:1">
              <section class="panel-section">
                <div class="section-header section-header--ruled"><h2 class="section-title">Phases</h2></div>
                <div class="panel-list">
                  <div class="list-row list-row--compact"><span class="geo-type-icon"><i data-lucide="book-open-text"></i></span><span class="list-label">Map Info</span><span class="badge badge--success">done</span></div>
                  <div class="list-row list-row--compact"><span class="geo-type-icon"><i data-lucide="settings-2"></i></span><span class="list-label">World</span><span class="badge badge--success">done</span></div>
                  <div class="list-row list-row--compact"><span class="geo-type-icon"><i data-lucide="users"></i></span><span class="list-label">Teams</span><span class="badge badge--success">done</span></div>
                  <div class="list-row list-row--compact list-row--selected"><span class="geo-type-icon"><i data-lucide="pickaxe"></i></span><span class="list-label">Build</span><span class="badge badge--neutral">current</span></div>
                  <div class="list-row list-row--compact"><span class="geo-type-icon"><i data-lucide="goal"></i></span><span class="list-label">Wools</span><span class="badge badge--dim">next</span></div>
                  <div class="list-row list-row--compact"><span class="geo-type-icon"><i data-lucide="badge-check"></i></span><span class="list-label">Review &amp; Export</span><span class="badge badge--dim">locked</span></div>
                </div>
              </section>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ds-example">
          <div class="ds-example-label">Sub-steps — the flow bar</div>
          <div class="ds-canvas-bar-example canvas-subbar">
            <div class="flow-steps">
              <button class="flow-step flow-step--done"><i data-lucide="check"></i>Colours</button>
              <button class="flow-step flow-step--done"><i data-lucide="check"></i>Spawn</button>
              <button class="flow-step flow-step--active">Room</button>
              <button class="flow-step">Monuments</button>
            </div>
            <div class="canvas-subbar-right"><span class="canvas-zoom">100%</span></div>
          </div>
          <p class="section-desc" style="margin-top:var(--space-3)">The flow bar shows where you are inside a
             phase — a check marks done, the accent underline marks the current sub-step. The rail jumps between
             phases; a phase stays locked until its prerequisites are met (Review needs a connected map).</p>
          <div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-2);margin-top:var(--space-2)">
            <button class="action-btn">Back</button>
            <button class="action-btn action-btn--primary">Next: Monuments</button>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ════════════════════════ 0 · MAP INFO ════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="ds-section" id="info">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="ds-kicker">00</p>
          <h2>Map Info — identity &amp; authors</h2>
        </div>
        <p>The minimum the generator needs before any geometry step: a name and at least one author.
           Version, gamemode, and objective are auto-derived and locked.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        The intent model's <code>meta</code> block carries the map's human-readable identity.
        <strong>Name</strong> and <strong>authors</strong> are the only required fields — everything else is
        fixed by convention (<code>version 1.0.0</code>), inferred from the step selection
        (<code>gamemode ctw</code>), or templated from the objectives contract (<code>objective</code>).
        Author usernames resolve to UUIDs via the Mojang API at save time; the inputs accept raw usernames
        during authoring.
      </p>

      <article class="ds-example">
        <div class="ds-example-label">Map Info workspace — identity + authors</div>
        <div class="ds-panel-frame">
          <div class="workspace-scroll">

            <section class="panel-section">
              <div class="section-header section-header--ruled">
                <h2 class="section-title">Identity</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="section-body">
                <div class="field">
                  <label class="field-label">Map Name <span class="field-required">*</span></label>
                  <input class="field-input" type="text" value="Thunder" placeholder="My CTW Map"/>
                </div>
                <div class="field-row">
                  <div class="field">
                    <label class="field-label">Version</label>
                    <input class="field-input" type="text" value="1.0.0" disabled title="Auto-derived"/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="field field--compact">
                    <label class="field-label">Mode</label>
                    <input class="field-input" type="text" value="ctw" disabled title="Auto-derived"/>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                  <label class="field-label">Objective</label>
                  <textarea class="field-input field-input--textarea" rows="2" disabled title="Auto-derived from gamemode">Capture the other teams' wools and take them to your victory monument to win.</textarea>
                </div>
                <p class="section-desc">Version, mode, and objective are auto-derived from the authoring context — they cannot be edited here.</p>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="panel-section">
              <div class="section-header section-header--ruled">
                <h2 class="section-title">Authors <span class="field-required">*</span></h2>
                <button class="action-btn">+ Add</button>
              </div>
              <div class="author-list">
                <div class="author-row">
                  <span class="author-avatar"></span>
                  <input class="field-input author-name" type="text" placeholder="Minecraft username"/>
                  <input class="field-input author-contribution" type="text" placeholder="Contribution (optional)"/>
                  <button class="btn-remove" title="Remove"><i data-lucide="x"></i></button>
                </div>
                <div class="author-row">
                  <span class="author-avatar"></span>
                  <input class="field-input author-name" type="text" placeholder="Minecraft username"/>
                  <input class="field-input author-contribution" type="text" value="Old XML"/>
                  <button class="btn-remove" title="Remove"><i data-lucide="x"></i></button>
                </div>
                <div class="author-row">
                  <span class="author-avatar"></span>
                  <input class="field-input author-name" type="text" placeholder="Minecraft username"/>
                  <input class="field-input author-contribution" type="text" value="Provided feedback for update"/>
                  <button class="btn-remove" title="Remove"><i data-lucide="x"></i></button>
                </div>
                <div class="author-row">
                  <span class="author-avatar"></span>
                  <input class="field-input author-name" type="text" placeholder="Minecraft username"/>
                  <input class="field-input author-contribution" type="text" value="Provided feedback for update"/>
                  <button class="btn-remove" title="Remove"><i data-lucide="x"></i></button>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="section-desc">Usernames resolve to UUIDs via the Mojang API at save. The lead author has no contribution label; contributors carry a short freeform note — thunder ships with one author and three contributors.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="panel-section">
              <div class="panel-actions">
                <button class="action-btn action-btn--primary">Save &amp; continue</button>
                <span class="panel-save-status">thunder_blank · unsaved</span>
              </div>
            </section>

          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <!-- ════════════════════════ 1 · WORLD ════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="ds-section" id="world">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="ds-kicker">01</p>
          <h2>World — detect terrain</h2>
        </div>
        <p>The blocks come first. Islands and symmetry are detected as neutral shapes; they seed the team
           count and spawn positions — so no step starts blank.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        A new map (<code>thunder_blank</code>) is a world with blocks but no <code>map.xml</code>. The
        read-side analyses run on that terrain and bridge the physical world to the logical intent. The
        <strong>y=0 footprint is the void-filter substrate</strong>: every column with a surface block is
        automatically buildable, so the terrain itself <em>is</em> the build area and <em>no region rows are
        generated for it</em>. Islands are detected as <strong>neutral shapes</strong> — the system does not
        know which team owns which island yet. Ownership is an authoring decision that happens in the Teams
        step, after the author defines their teams.
      </p>

      <article class="ds-example">
        <div class="ds-example-label">World workspace — terrain analysis · all islands neutral</div>
        <div class="ds-workspace-frame">
