    <!-- ════════════════════════ 2 · TEAMS & SPAWNS ════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="ds-section" id="teams">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="ds-kicker">02</p>
          <h2>Teams &amp; Spawns</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Define team 0 once — symmetry orbit fills the rest, the spawn protection is auto-wired. Assign
           islands to set the orbit order.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        In the intent model a team's <em>spawn point</em> and its <em>protection zone</em> are one unit,
        defined once for the authored team (team 0 · Blue). The system uses the confirmed <code>rot_90</code>
        symmetry to rotate that unit onto the other three orbit positions, then auto-wires the
        <code>enter = only-&lt;team&gt;</code> filter on each protection zone. After defining teams, the
        author tags islands to teams as <strong>authoring help</strong>: this fixes the <em>orbit order</em>
        (the sequence the map was laid out in) and seats each team's spawn on the right island. Islands are
        neutral by default — not every island needs a team. Thunder's centre island stays
