    <section class="ds-section" id="build">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="ds-kicker">03</p>
          <h2>Build</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Terrain is auto-buildable via the void filter — draw only the over-void bridges, set the max
           height in the side view, and the generator unions them and enforces the rest.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="ds-theming-note">
        PGM's void filter makes every column that has a surface block automatically editable, so the islands'
        terrain <strong>is</strong> the build area — no region rows are generated for it.
        <code>BuildIntent.Areas</code> are therefore only the <em>over-void extensions</em>: the bridges and
        platforms you want buildable across the gaps between islands. Set the max build height here (thunder =
        <strong>Y 25</strong>), mark the bridges, and the generator unions them and applies the void filter to
        the <code>negative</code>. Inner cut-outs (holes) are supported as a <code>complement</code>.
      </p>

